Package com.ubicua.didas.userprofile

Class DidasUserProfileProviderFactory

java.lang.Object
org.keycloak.userprofile.DeclarativeUserProfileProviderFactory
com.ubicua.didas.userprofile.DidasUserProfileProviderFactory
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.keycloak.component.AmphibianProviderFactory<org.keycloak.userprofile.UserProfileProvider>, org.keycloak.component.ComponentFactory<org.keycloak.userprofile.UserProfileProvider,org.keycloak.userprofile.UserProfileProvider>, org.keycloak.provider.ConfiguredProvider, org.keycloak.provider.ProviderFactory<org.keycloak.userprofile.UserProfileProvider>, org.keycloak.userprofile.UserProfileProviderFactory
public class DidasUserProfileProviderFactory extends org.keycloak.userprofile.DeclarativeUserProfileProviderFactory
Factory for the Didas user profile provider, extending DeclarativeUserProfileProviderFactory.

It is responsible for parsing and applying realm-specific JSON configuration (UPConfig), initializing default user profile metadata for all contexts, and exposing provider configuration properties in the Admin Console.

Lifecycle

  • init(Scope) – loads system or realm UPConfig, sets up read-only validators, and registers metadata for each context.
  • validateConfiguration(KeycloakSession, RealmModel, ComponentModel) – validates JSON against schema and clears cache on changes.
  • create(KeycloakSession) – creates runtime instances of DidasUserProfileProvider.
  • postInit(KeycloakSessionFactory) and close() – no-op.
Author:
Ivan Kuchumov
